description: The floor tiles of the Cathedral seem to become chipped here, as
small flakes appear to scatter as your feet brush up against them.
Small portraits line the walls of this hall as well, the faces
contained within them seeming to leer at you from within their frames.
The sickening feeling that these paintings were made on canvases of
human skin does not help to ease this sensation.  The vaulted ceilings
to the west give way to something of a humbler size to the east, and
exits can be found in all directions.
55343.name: Sanctuary Entrance

description: You are in a whirlwind, where objects fly past you and into you!
The great storm pulls at you, tearing at your clothing and equipment
mercilessly.  As the wind subsides for a moment, you are able to
examine your surroundings.  The storm continues in all directions
except below you, where The Sanctuary of the Cathedral lies.  As you
are about to take action to escape, the storm tugs at you again...!

description: Great blocks of stone and gravel block the way leading down to the
Catacombs.  Moss grows on the soil here, and the air is still.  Small
alcoves line the walls, shallowly filled in with dirt from the
avalanche.  Above, the tunnel continues undaunted by the cave-in that
must have happened here years ago.
